    "what_description": "Calendula officinalis is a perennial herbaceous plant that belongs to the family Asteraceae. It has bright orange to yellow daisy-like flowers with 12-20 petals, 30-40 mm in diameter, and a central disc of 100-150 florets. The leaves are 50-150 mm long, lance-shaped, and have an acute tip. The stem is erect, 30-100 cm tall, and green with a reddish tint at the base. The plant is native to the Mediterranean region and has been naturalized in many parts of the world.",
