    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Calendula officinalis are burns, where the anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties help reduce pain and prevent infection. Eczema sufferers can also benefit from its soothing effects, which reduce inflammation and promote skin regeneration. Skin irritation, such as from insect bites, is alleviated by its antioxidant properties, which neutralize free radicals and promote healing. Minor cuts and bruises can be treated with Calendula officinalis, as its antimicrobial properties prevent infection and promote wound healing. Calendula officinalis has also been effective in treating acne, sunburn, wound infection, fungal infections, rashes, chapped lips, herpes, skin ulcers, psoriasis, boils, rosacea, wound healing, and diaper rash.",
