    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Calendula officinalis are antimicrobial, which inhibit the growth of bacteria, fungi, and other pathogens. The anti-inflammatory properties of this plant help reduce swelling and pain in various conditions, including wound healing and skin irritations. Additionally, the antioxidant properties of Calendula officinalis protect cells from oxidative damage, contributing to its ability to promote wound healing. The antiseptic properties of this plant also play a crucial role in wound healing by preventing infection and promoting tissue repair. The bioactive compounds responsible for these medicinal properties include flavonoids, triterpenoids, and volatile oils, such as isovaleric acid and isovaleryl ester.",
