    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Calendula officinalis are typically obtained through various extraction methods, resulting in products such as calendula salve, a topical balm often used to soothe skin irritations and wounds due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which are enhanced by the presence of triterpenoid saponins and sesquiterpene lactones. Calendula cream, on the other hand, provides a moisturizing effect and is commonly used to treat skin conditions like eczema and dermatitis due to its ability to reduce inflammation and promote wound healing. Calendula tincture, a liquid extract, is often used internally to alleviate digestive issues such as constipation and diarrhea, while calendula ointment serves as a protective barrier on the skin's surface, shielding it from external irritants. Calendula oil, derived from the plant's flowers, is rich in fatty acids and is frequently used as a carrier oil in aromatherapy and skincare products due to its emollient and anti-inflammatory properties. These preparations are valued for their ability to promote tissue repair, reduce inflammation, and soothe skin irritations, making Calendula officinalis a popular choice in herbal medicine.",
