    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Calendula officinalis improperly include inducing allergic reactions in individuals with sensitivities to the plant's compounds, particularly the sesquiterpene lactones, which can cause an immune response. Improper use may also lead to skin irritation due to the essential oil's high concentration of camphor and borneol, potentially causing redness, itching, and inflammation. Furthermore, using Calendula officinalis may interact with medications, such as blood thinners and diabetes medications, due to its potential anti-inflammatory and anticoagulant properties, which can alter medication efficacy or increase the risk of bleeding. Additionally, improper use of Calendula officinalis may trigger digestive issues, including stomach upset and diarrhea, in individuals with pre-existing gastrointestinal conditions or those taking certain medications. In rare cases, skin irritation can occur due to the essential oil's high concentration of camphor and borneol."
